                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>
                        <button class="faq-toggle" aria-expanded="false">
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                            How does the X-S20 compare to the X-T5?
                        </button>
                    </h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>
                            The X-S20 offers better video (6.2K, Vlog mode), larger battery, and costs $400 less. The X-T5 has higher resolution (40MP vs 26MP) and dual SD slots. For hybrid shooters, the X-S20 is often the better choice.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>
                        <button class="faq-toggle" aria-expanded="false">
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                            Does the X-S20 overheat during video?
                        </button>
                    </h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>
                            No, heat management is excellent. Continuous 4K 60p for 90+ minutes without overheating. Even 6.2K 30p can record 60+ minutes at normal temperatures.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>
                        <button class="faq-toggle" aria-expanded="false">
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                            Who should buy the X-S20?
                        </button>
                    </h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>
                            Content creators, YouTubers, hybrid shooters, and enthusiasts who want professional features without professional prices. Skip it if you need maximum resolution (X-T5) or fastest burst rates (X-H2S).
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>
                        <button class="faq-toggle" aria-expanded="false">
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                            What memory cards work best?
                        </button>
                    </h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>
                            For 6.2K video, use UHS-II V90 SD cards (minimum 250MB/s write). Recommended: SanDisk Extreme Pro or Sony SF-G Tough. For 4K 60p, V60 cards work excellently.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Author Box -->
        <section class="section author-box" style="background: var(--bg-soft); border-radius: 12px; padding: 24px; margin-top: 32px;">
            <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; align-items: flex-start;">
                <img src="/assets/images/team-avatar.webp" alt="cameraupick Editorial Team" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; border-radius: 50%; object-fit: contain; background: white; border: 2px solid var(--accent); padding: 4px;">
